request.description:
This example shows how to populate a environment variables from a sample JSON response using a custom function in JavaScript.  

This functionality is useful when you would like to extract data from complex object definitions in the return JSON schema.  Additionally, manipulation of the data can be performed before the variable is populated.

The function definition is:
```
var my_function = function(resp, arguments...) {
  ...
  return x || undefined;
}
```

Please review the Test script comments.  Sending the request will perform the requested actions and populate variables you can review.

A reference item that implements a delay for the poller.  This item can be copied and modified as needed, however, the Test script must include the following code for the poller to work:

```
eval(postman.getGlobalVariable("_f5_workflow_functions"));
f5_poll_next();
```
